      "content": "i get the \"diversified mix\" thing, but when you look at the scale of the problem and how fast we need to cut carbon, it feels like renewables just aren't enough on their own. it's almost like there's no other realistic option if we actually want to hit those targets. isn't it more of a factual necessity than just an \"option\" at this point?",
