      "content": "While renewables are essential, they are not a \"factual necessity\" on their own because they cannot provide the massive, consistent baseload power required to meet aggressive climate targets without significant grid infrastructure upgrades. The reality is that we need a hybrid approach where nuclear provides the stable backbone while renewables handle the variable load, making the combination the only realistic path forward.",
